<subSubSection id="1D6700FE303303A085DCFE99D9C2554E" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="25055391B16C8D23DF1A558C06D63836" pageNumber="19">
Species of the scorpionfish genus 
<taxonomicName id="09F4D54576B1E70681996D1B5B1238EF" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:0707F8C9-8786-4D4C-8F2F-D9F66C7B96BF" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sebastidae" genus="Trachyscorpia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Trachyscorpia Ginsburg 1953:23, 57" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageNumber="19" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Trachyscorpia</taxonomicName>
are deepwater, bottom dwelling, relatively large fishes, attaining at least 35 cm standard length. The genus was originally proposed for 
<taxonomicName id="D96EFA16DC63C39FDC3F1D467ECF86F7" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:11430FA5-4F14-4077-9B05-5A5B1ACD7763" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Scorpaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Scorpaena cristulata Goode &amp; Bean 1896:246" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageNumber="19" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cristulata">Scorpaena cristulata Goode &amp; Bean, 1896</taxonomicName>
by Ginsburg (1953) who simultaneously included 
<taxonomicName id="DAABD279E933810AFC9B008B6BFB010A" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:6890D1BD-3149-4125-B41F-8C0DE4ED9144" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Scorpaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Scorpaena echinata Köhler 1896:478" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageNumber="19" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="echinata">Scorpaena echinata Koehler, 1896</taxonomicName>
in the genus. Subsequently, Eschmeyer (1969) added 
<taxonomicName id="E7C566F07F7C8B769278732B0AB17CC4" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:607CEBB9-2FD7-454C-AFB3-E569BBD4C7A0" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Scorpaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Scorpaena capensis Gmelin 1789:1219" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageNumber="19" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="capensis">Scorpaena capensis Gilchrist &amp; von Bonde, 1924</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="0729584AC4641B5C327939AC6A2B74B0" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:0707F8C9-8786-4D4C-8F2F-D9F66C7B96BF" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sebastidae" genus="Trachyscorpia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Trachyscorpia Ginsburg 1953:23, 57" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageNumber="19" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Trachyscorpia</taxonomicName>
. Eschmeyer (1969) tentatively regarded 
<taxonomicName id="92AD599DD9D234ABC4D7038C5300A1D7" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sebastidae" genus="Trachyscorpia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageNumber="19" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cristulata">T. cristulata</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="792858F248400BED4D223F242FBF45B3" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sebastidae" genus="Trachyscorpia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageNumber="19" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="echinata">T. echinata</taxonomicName>
as the subspecies, 
<taxonomicName id="67A86BA6B55A36567824F3C688D929A3" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sebastidae" genus="Trachyscorpia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageNumber="19" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="cristulata" subSpecies="cristulata">T. cristulata cristulata</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E73CD37FC47049D39CD3970890DF98CD" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sebastidae" genus="Trachyscorpia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageNumber="19" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="cristulata" subSpecies="echinata">T. c. echinata</taxonomicName>
. He also separated the species of 
<taxonomicName id="BC4DB1723DC5D2071D5412497E13D978" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:0707F8C9-8786-4D4C-8F2F-D9F66C7B96BF" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sebastidae" genus="Trachyscorpia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Trachyscorpia Ginsburg 1953:23, 57" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageNumber="19" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Trachyscorpia</taxonomicName>
into two subgenera, 
<taxonomicName id="14903B20D9A3BF3955176D66AE55EAD0" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sebastidae" genus="Trachyscorpia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageNumber="19" phylum="Chordata" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Trachyscorpia">Trachyscorpia</taxonomicName>
(type species: 
<taxonomicName id="508788084C55B43A8104D3A5D2568C2F" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sebastidae" genus="Trachyscorpia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageNumber="19" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cristulata">T. cristulata</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="759C4B696FE6D8424EBDE7D19D2CD2C9" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:D5DE802B-B69B-40F4-B1AA-BF04007442BA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sebastidae" genus="Trachyscorpia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Mesoscorpia Trachyscorpia Eschmeyer 1969:50" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageNumber="19" phylum="Chordata" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Mesoscorpia">Mesoscorpia</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="95CA0FDEA8BA11B9FFF39C90B534D2D7" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sebastidae" genus="Trachyscorpia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageNumber="19" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="capensis">T. capensis</taxonomicName>
), the latter being his new subgenus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B9DFC9A4E1FFCEF94ED105E6E346212F" pageNumber="19">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="1B50D4A0BEE9C207807BD8F2BD433258" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:0707F8C9-8786-4D4C-8F2F-D9F66C7B96BF" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sebastidae" genus="Trachyscorpia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Trachyscorpia Ginsburg 1953:23, 57" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageNumber="19" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Trachyscorpia</taxonomicName>
is characterized by the following combination of characters: occiput flat, lacking pit; first preopercular spine largest; head bones strongly ossified; suborbital ridge well developed, with usually 5 or more spines; palatine teeth present; dorsal-fin spines 12 or 13; vertebrae 25 or 26; pectoral-fin margin bilobed; lateral line complete, extending onto caudal-fin base; and scales on the body ctenoid (Eschmeyer, 1969; this study).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BA9DB313DDCA3438529B8EDA48F5DC0A" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicName id="9F5221FE49F9D6D0B10D5FF0543B7E25" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sebastidae" genus="Trachyscorpia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageNumber="19" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="capensis">Trachyscorpia capensis</taxonomicName>
was described as a new species of 
<taxonomicName id="4E945843798F359360938C047F99981F" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Scorpaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageNumber="19" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Scorpaena</taxonomicName>
from the west coast of South Africa from three specimens (whereabouts of the syntypes currently unknown; e.g., Eschmeyer, 1998). Although the name 
<taxonomicName id="4544857273FA304B0BA8A4F4380BCFE1" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sebastidae" genus="Trachyscorpia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageNumber="19" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="capensis">T. capensis</taxonomicName>
has been used in many publications since Eschmeyer (1969) (e.g., Eschmeyer, 1986; Ishida, 1990; Pakhorukov, 2001), 
<taxonomicName id="82BAE54FFE5E20415E5FD0651D39AF19" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sebastidae" genus="Trachyscorpia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageNumber="19" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="capensis">T. capensis</taxonomicName>
is permanently invalid because it was preoccupied by 
<taxonomicName id="710CFD0AEAD18EAA1E5835B990F69C08" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:607CEBB9-2FD7-454C-AFB3-E569BBD4C7A0" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Scorpaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Scorpaena capensis Gmelin 1789:1219" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageNumber="19" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="capensis">Scorpaena capensis Gmelin, 1789</taxonomicName>
, which is currently recognized as 
<taxonomicName id="B7F4D72CE767A1086BCB0D336D1AD2B4" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sebastidae" genus="Sebastes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageNumber="19" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="capensis">Sebastes capensis</taxonomicName>
. Whitley (1970) proposed a replacement name, 
<taxonomicName id="C73D53366A13A08098A905531CAB639E" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CF345025-EF7E-432B-B370-B010B63DB47E" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sebastidae" genus="Trachyscorpia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Trachyscorpia Mesoscorpia eschmeyeri Whitley 1970:245" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageNumber="19" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="eschmeyeri">T. eschmeyeri</taxonomicName>
, for Gilchrist and von Bonde’s 
<taxonomicName id="25D2DDF6965A412442C6F363955C7CE4" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:607CEBB9-2FD7-454C-AFB3-E569BBD4C7A0" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Scorpaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Scorpaena capensis Gmelin 1789:1219" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageNumber="19" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="capensis">Scorpaena capensis</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D252278F39DC8E2E9E28043AEE6182D6" pageNumber="20">
The species of 
<taxonomicName id="4248AC353CB6A0341C58E2339194BD03" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:0707F8C9-8786-4D4C-8F2F-D9F66C7B96BF" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sebastidae" genus="Trachyscorpia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Trachyscorpia Ginsburg 1953:23, 57" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Trachyscorpia</taxonomicName>
from Australasian waters (mostly reported as 
<taxonomicName id="CCE7249F22AC824BDDD8855543F19CBA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sebastidae" genus="Trachyscorpia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="capensis">T. capensis</taxonomicName>
) has been recognized as containing two sympatric morphotypes by several ichthyologists for a long time (e.g., Daley et al, 1997; A. Stewart and C. Paulin, pers. comm., 2004). Our further examinations of specimens from the region showed that the two morphotypes represent 
<taxonomicName id="8E69332A7A30EB229A9EA2B48263E1F9" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CF345025-EF7E-432B-B370-B010B63DB47E" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sebastidae" genus="Trachyscorpia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Trachyscorpia Mesoscorpia eschmeyeri Whitley 1970:245" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="eschmeyeri" subGenus="Mesoscorpia">T. (M.) eschmeyeri</taxonomicName>
and a distinct new species of 
<taxonomicName id="10F4E2B1563EAF0EEEAEF001EFEC23D9" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:D5DE802B-B69B-40F4-B1AA-BF04007442BA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sebastidae" genus="Trachyscorpia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Mesoscorpia Trachyscorpia Eschmeyer 1969:50" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Mesoscorpia">Trachyscorpia (Mesoscorpia)</taxonomicName>
. In addition, during examination of the Australasian specimens, another new species was found at the Australian National Fish Collection (CSIRO). This new species was collected from the South-West Indian Ridge, southwestern Indian Ocean (ca. 1,700 km south of the southern tip of Madagascar), and resembles the Australasian new species rather than 
<taxonomicName id="4820CC1A3003100E37C3B053D2148166" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CF345025-EF7E-432B-B370-B010B63DB47E" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sebastidae" genus="Trachyscorpia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Trachyscorpia Mesoscorpia eschmeyeri Whitley 1970:245" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="eschmeyeri" subGenus="Mesoscorpia">T. (M.) eschmeyeri</taxonomicName>
. The two new species are herein described in detail, along with a redefinition of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="AC06F795CD6450BC710C3F1FD8BB7FF0" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:D5DE802B-B69B-40F4-B1AA-BF04007442BA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sebastidae" genus="Trachyscorpia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Mesoscorpia Trachyscorpia Eschmeyer 1969:50" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Mesoscorpia">Mesoscorpia</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
